data.name: label52.Text
data.value: Here you can adjust engine's rpm's, having specified in what rpm's there will be a switching of gears, what rpm's of the engine should be on neutral gear, and the maximum gears of the engine for the current car.

data.name: label49.Text
data.value: Change the adjustment ECU with the help ScrollBars (TrackBars). The value choice over ScrollBars (TrackBars) allows to increase strongly capacity of giving of fuel that is not recommended so u can make your car stronger.

data.name: label50.Text
data.value: Change the adjustment Turbo like ECU. It's simply, like in Dyno tuning.

data.name: label19.Text
data.value: First you need to select file GlobalB.lzc from GLOBALB folder in the NFSU2 directory, then u can select car and change car performance.

data.name: label53.Text
data.value: The fields intended for manual editing, that is that field where you can enter values, should contain ONLY NUMBERS FROM 0 TO 255. Letters and other signs will be ignored. As well as it is more than number 255.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value: It is possible to "take" handling from any other car from game, for this purpose choose it from the list and press to "Apply"

data.name: label16.Text
data.value: In the next versions of the program to regulate values it will not be necessary manually. There will be a simple adjustment with help TrackBars and/or pictures, like in game. If you have any ideas for this program, write to us, our contacts and e-mail you will find in the "Help" section.

data.name: label51.Text
data.value: The car drive defines a leading axis at the current car, at a full upgrade (3 level). For example, if it is the drag-car it is necessary to put a back drive(RWD), for drift, back(RWD) or full(4WD). Though in Underground2 drift on a forward drive(FWD) goes well, though in a real life it is silly and it is almost unreal.

data.name: label9.Text
data.value: The car suspension bracket very strongly influences on handling. Too high suspension bracket will disturb on turns, but any noob player can do wheelie :D Do not put too low suspension bracket, differently the car will disappear!

data.name: label61.Text
data.value: Wheels width influences coupling with road. Wheels position influences handling and stability at driving. Try to avoid too wide and a narrow position.
